End-to-end flow
 Start the launcher flow

The flow starts in the main launcher flow.

It uses these input variables:
route_intent
route_user_role
route_req_msr
auth_failed

These inputs are used to decide where the caller should go.

2. Fetch Destination

The flow calls the Fetch Destination module.

This module:
clears old destination attributes
calls the Destination Lookup Lambda
returns destination details

Inputs:
route_intent
route_user_role
route_req_msr
auth_failed

Outputs:
dest_transfer_type
dest_auth_required
dest_payload
dest_id
dest_name
dest_desc
dest_hoops_name

This step decides:
what destination to use
whether authentication is required
what routing payload should be used

3. Check whether authentication is required

After Fetch Destination, the flow checks:
dest_auth_required == true

If authentication is not required:
continue to the next step

If authentication is required:
go to the authentication branch

4. Check whether caller already passed MFA

The flow checks whether the caller already completed authentication earlier.

If already authenticated:
continue

If not authenticated:
invoke the authentication module

5. Authenticate caller

The authentication module:
asks for caller or member details
validates identity
sets authentication result values

Possible results:

If authentication succeeds:
continue to the next stage

If authentication fails:
set auth_failed = true
return to the launcher or fallback logic

6. Get member or subscriber flags

After successful authentication, the flow gets member or subscriber flags.

Purpose:
enrich caller context
provide data needed for personalization

7. Personalization

The flow invokes the Personalization module.

This step decides whether the current route should stay the same or change.

Possible results:
no change
new route or new intent
launch another specialized path

8. Evaluate personalization result

After personalization, the flow evaluates the result.

Possible outcomes:
continue with the current route
switch to another intent or path

9. Update Phone Number

After personalization, the flow invokes the Update Phone Number module.

10. Check what happened in Update Phone Number

Immediately after Update Phone Number, the flow checks:
upph_return_reason

The check block asks:
What happened in Update Phone module?

There are 3 possible outcomes.

11. If upph_return_reason = done

Path:
Update Phone Number
check upph_return_reason
done
Invoke Router

Meaning:
the phone update completed successfully
the flow goes directly to Invoke Router

12. If upph_return_reason = not-applicable

Path:
Update Phone Number
check upph_return_reason
not-applicable
MSAT Survey Offer
Invoke Router

Meaning:
phone update does not apply
the flow offers MSAT Survey
then continues to Invoke Router

13. If upph_return_reason = switch-intent

Path:
Update Phone Number
check upph_return_reason
switch-intent
Intent Switch

Meaning:
the phone update step decided the intent should change
the flow goes to Intent Switch instead of routing immediately

14. Invoke Router

The Invoke Router module starts at:
Start Invoke Router

Then it goes to:
Launch Destination (Reporting)

From Launch Destination (Reporting), two visible paths are shown.

15. Routing path

The flow goes from Launch Destination (Reporting) to Routing Service.

Routing Service also receives input from Routing Payload.

So this path is:
Start Invoke Router
Launch Destination (Reporting)
Routing Service
Routing Payload is passed into Routing Service

16. Event publishing path

From Launch Destination (Reporting), the flow also goes downward to:
Publish Event
Call State Pub

So this path is:
Launch Destination (Reporting)
Publish Event
Call State Pub

17. Complete normal path

The normal routing path is:

Start Launcher
Fetch Destination
Check whether authentication is required
Authenticate caller if needed
Get member or subscriber flags
Personalization
Update Phone Number
Check upph_return_reason
if done, go to Invoke Router
Launch Destination (Reporting)
Routing Service using Routing Payload
Publish Event
Call State Pub

18. Path when phone update is not applicable

Start Launcher
Fetch Destination
Check whether authentication is required
Authenticate caller if needed
Get member or subscriber flags
Personalization
Update Phone Number
Check upph_return_reason
if not-applicable, go to MSAT Survey Offer
then go to Invoke Router
Launch Destination (Reporting)
Routing Service using Routing Payload
Publish Event
Call State Pub

19. Path when phone update switches intent

Start Launcher
Fetch Destination
Check whether authentication is required
Authenticate caller if needed
Get member or subscriber flags
Personalization
Update Phone Number
Check upph_return_reason
if switch-intent, go to Intent Switch

Compact plain text flow

Start Launcher
Fetch Destination
Check auth required
If needed, authenticate caller
Get member flags
Personalization
Update Phone Number
Check upph_return_reason

If done:
go to Invoke Router

If not-applicable:
go to MSAT Survey Offer
then go to Invoke Router

If switch-intent:
go to Intent Switch

Inside Invoke Router:
Start Invoke Router
Launch Destination (Reporting)
send Routing Payload to Routing Service
publish event
send event to Call State Pub

